{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 17:06:13.610444", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission details\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty devices: server_access_router\n- Root cause: http_acl_block\n\nRationale (concise)\n- Only host 10.2.1.13 fails TCP/80/443 to 10.200.0.0/24; others succeed.\n- ICMP and routing healthy; SYNs sent from the client remain in SYN-SENT, implying silent drop.\n- Server farm listeners are up; iptables defaults show ACCEPT on most nodes. Most consistent with a selective L3/L4 filter (ACL) on the server edge affecting this source for HTTP/HTTPS.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2805, "output_tokens": 132, "total_tokens": 2937, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2688}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
